{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Regulators are wrong to water down tough mortgage standards.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by policy expert Peter J Wallison contends looser mortgage-underwriting standards, supported by Congress and community activists as means of encouraging home-buying, actually have opposite effect; holds such standards drive home prices up while encouraging buyers to take greater risks; says low standards help home builders and real estate agents, but not potential owners, and that policy makers would be wise to consider this.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "25", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"lastname": "WALLISON", "rank": 1, "firstname": "Peter", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "J."}], "original": "By PETER J. WALLISON", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/01/opinion/underwriting-the-next-housing-crisis.html", "lead_paragraph": "Regulators are wrong to water down tough mortgage standards.", "headline": {"main": "Underwriting the Next Housing Crisis", "print_headline": "Underwriting the Next Housing Crisis", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "54542b1238f0d839202e9b3f", "word_count": "804", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/11/01/opinion/1101OPEDmenchin/1101OPEDmenchin-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/11/01/opinion/1101OPEDmenchin/1101OPEDmenchin-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 782, "url": "images/2014/11/01/opinion/1101OPEDmenchin/1101OPEDmenchin-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/11/01/opinion/1101OPEDmenchin/1101OPEDmenchin-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "782"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/11/01/opinion/1101OPEDmenchin/1101OPEDmenchin-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2014/11